[A listeriosis outbreak has involved so far at least 3 deaths and 29 illnesses in 10 US states and has now been linked to eating Happy Valley Brand Caramel Apples made by the Happy Apple Company, which has manufacturing facilities are located in Orosi, California and Union, Missouri. Happy Apple Brand Caramel Apples have been sold at multiple retail, discount, and club store locations in 31 US states.

According to the 1st news report above, 2 Canadians have also developed listeriosis caused by listeria with the same genotype as a US outbreak strain. We are not told if the Canadian patients ate caramel apples while in the US or if contaminated caramel apples had been exported from the US and obtained locally in Canada. The recalled Happy Valley Caramel Apples were pre-packaged in clear, plastic containers, as a single, 3-, 4- or 8-pack. No illnesses have been associated with uncoated apples or caramel candy, or with caramel apples that are not prepackaged, according to the CDC.

For a discussion of listeriosis, please see my comments in ProMED-mail post Listeriosis, fatal - USA: (CO) 20110605.1719.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3055407,12. - Mod.ML]
